<subSubSection id="24CB1080FFB9FFE7FAB2ADC382F5FC9F" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6C6E430BFFB9FFE7FAB2ADC382F5FC9F" blockId="13.[151,1437,541,892]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFB9FFE7FAB2ADC3815EFD23" bold="true" box="[199,315,685,711]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFB9FFE7FB37ADC38251FD23" authorityName="Carvalho-Batista, Terossi, Zara, Mantelatto &amp; Costa" authorityYear="2020" box="[322,564,685,711]" class="Malacostraca" family="Penaeidae" genus="Xiphopenaeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dincao">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFB9FFE7FB37ADC38251FD23" box="[322,564,685,711]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Xiphopenaeus dincao</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recently described and the only record from 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FFB9FFE7FE2BADC384B7FD23" box="[1118,1234,685,711]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, under the current name, was collected in Cananéia (see above) and appear in the species description (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFB9FFE7FE3EADBF85F4FD0F" author="Carvalho-Batista, A. &amp; Terossi, M. &amp; Zara, F. J. &amp; Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Costa, R. C." box="[1099,1425,721,748]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="15281" refId="ref56822" refString="Carvalho-Batista, A., Terossi, M., Zara, F. J., Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Costa, R. C. (2019) A multigene and morphological analysis expands the diversity of the seabod shrimp Xiphopenaeus Smith, 1869 (Decapoda: Penaeidae), with descriptions of two new species. Scientific Reports, 9, 15281. https: // doi. org / 10.1038 / s 41598 - 019 - 51484 - 3" type="journal article" year="2019">
Carvalho-Batista 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFB9FFE7FF66ADBC8520FD0F" box="[1299,1349,721,747]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
). However, there are some previous records from 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FFB9FFE7F8CDAD9B8348FCEB" box="[696,813,757,783]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, which were discovered through molecular studies performed with samples from Ubatuba and Cananéia as 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFB9FFE7F88BAC7783B8FCD7" box="[766,989,793,820]" class="Malacostraca" family="Penaeidae" genus="Xiphopenaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undefined-2">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFB9FFE7F88BAC7783F8FCD7" box="[766,925,793,819]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Xiphopenaeus</emphasis>
sp. 2
